<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>RLST 24567.  Islamic Psychology.  100 Units.</strong></p><p class="courseblockdesc">
An exploration of the growing body of secondary literature on Islamic psychology. Relevant premodern approaches to mental well-being, rooted in scriptural, theological, philosophical, and mystical sources will be examined alongside contemporary literature that synthesizes modern psychology with Islamic teachings. No Arabic required.</p><p class="courseblockdetail">
