<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>RLST 24920.  Platonic Theologies.  100 Units.</strong></p><p class="courseblockdesc">
This course will examine the platonic theologies of Simone Weil, Iris Murdoch, and Robert Adams, with an eye to answering questions such as the following: what qualifies a theology as 'platonic'? What is the role of contemplation in such theologies? How do they approach metaphysics, ethics, and politics?</p><p class="courseblockdetail">
Instructor(s): Kevin Hector     Terms Offered: Spring<br/>
