<div class="courseblock main">
<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>RLST 25706.  Climate Justice.  100 Units.</strong></p><p class="courseblockdesc">
Climate injustice includes the disproportionate effects of climate change on people who benefit little from the activities that cause it, generally the poor, people of color, and people marginalized in other ways. Given the complex economic, physical, social, and political realities of climate change, what might climate justice entail? This course explores this complex question through an examination of classical and contemporary theories of justice; the gendered, colonial, and racial dimensions of climate change; and climate justice movements.</p><p class="courseblockdetail">
Instructor(s): Sarah Fredericks     Terms Offered: Winter<br/>
Note(s): Graduates may enroll only with permission of the instructor.<br/>
Equivalent Course(s): HMRT 25706, PBPL 25706, ENST 25706, GNSE 25702, CEGU 25706, KNOW 25706, RDIN 25706, GLST 25766<br/>
</p>
